# PR Netlify deploys (not in git)

Every pull request needs both:

1. A **playable app** at `https://pet-village-pr-{N}.netlify.app`
2. A **player-facing HTML explanation** at `https://pet-village-pr-{N}-explain.netlify.app`

Not just Markdown/HTML in the GitHub PR body.

**Do not commit** explain HTML, PR app builds, or Netlify state into this repo (`netlify-site/`, `pr*/`, `dist/` for PR previews, gh-pages artifacts, etc.). Build in temp folders, deploy, then discard locally.

For the full release ritual (version bump, tests, both deploys), follow `.agents/skills/pet-village-feature-release/SKILL.md`.

## Playable app

1. Build a **root-hosted** preview (do **not** deploy normal `dist/` — its `/pet-village/` base breaks Netlify):
   ```sh
   npm run build -- --base=/ --outDir=/tmp/pet-village-pr-{N}-app --emptyOutDir
   ```
2. Create or reuse a Netlify site named exactly `pet-village-pr-{N}` (e.g. PR 53 → `pet-village-pr-53`).
3. Deploy:
   ```sh
   npx --yes netlify-cli@26.2.0 deploy --prod --no-build --dir=/tmp/pet-village-pr-{N}-app --site=<app-site-id>
   ```
4. Load `https://pet-village-pr-{N}.netlify.app` and confirm `/` plus every browser-requested script, stylesheet, module chunk, font, and image required by the page returns HTTP 200. One representative asset is not sufficient.

## Explain page

1. Write the page in a **temp dir** (e.g. `/tmp/pet-village-pr-{N}-explain/index.html`) in the PR-38 explain style:
   - Fonts: Press Start 2P + VT323
   - Sections: pill, TL;DR card, What changed, How to try it, Verification, PR link
2. Create or reuse a Netlify site named `pet-village-pr-{N}-explain` (e.g. `pet-village-pr-51-explain`).
3. Deploy **from the temp dir only**:
   ```sh
   npx --yes netlify-cli@26.2.0 deploy --prod --no-build --dir=/tmp/pet-village-pr-{N}-explain --site=<explain-site-id>
   ```
4. Leave the working tree clean of explain-page files — never `git add` them.

## GitHub PR body

Keep the GitHub description short. Prefer linking both Netlify URLs:

```markdown
**Playable app:** https://pet-village-pr-53.netlify.app
**Explain:** https://pet-village-pr-53-explain.netlify.app

## Summary
- …
```

Do **not** treat the GitHub body as the primary HTML artifact — that lives on Netlify only.

